messages.content: You and Aras Karaitis are celebrating 6 years of friendship on Facebook
sounds good, let me know when you make it out this way
Haha definitely. Now I'm in Michigan for a week or so, but I'll let you know when I'm out by Chicago again
Haha sounds logical, but yea we should meet up soon, I am excited tpo hear about your time in the RMI

Haha you'll have to tell me more about it in person. I actually moved to Northwest Indiana. When I realized that my favorite thing to do in Chicago was go fishing at the Humboldt Park lagoon, I knew it was time to move out of the city. But I'll still be in Chicago quite a bit
Are you living in Humboldt park?
Yea lol I am at work right now
Cool. Did you get a job there?
I just moved to Chicago a few weeks ago, I am living with my brother right now in the South Loop
I'm back from Majuro. We should meet up sometime in the next month. Are you living in Detroit or Chicago?
Haha yeah, I think the whole job will be very Marshallese
Wow that's awesome, that job search sounds so Marshallese I'm glad it worked out I'm jealous.

Cool. Good luck finding a job. I got a gig teaching marine biology in Arrak, by Laura. I just emailed a bunch of people at CMI, and even though many of the emails didn't even go through, I eventually got offered the marine biology job. And then when I was trying to find out what the job would actually consist of, I kept getting referred to different people, until someone emailed me that I should 'just contact Stanley - he's in charge of everything.' And it was Stanley Lorennij. So I'll have the same boss as before, although I don't think he has much to do with the marine bio class. And I'll be living with Grandy. It should be fun.

Wow that's exciting what are u going to be doing in the Marshall islands? I'm still in Detroit but I just finished my interview process for a job in Chicago and am hoping to hear positive news but will see.
Hey, I'm going to the Marshall Islands this summer. I leave in a couple weeks. Just thought I'd let you know. We'll have to hang out sometime when I get back in August. Have you switched jobs yet?
